# macOS Swift audio helper

Preferred capture: bundled `audiocapture-helper` with **CoreAudio process tap** on macOS 14.2+; falls back to Swift ScreenCaptureKit, then PyObjC ScreenCaptureKit.

## stdout / stderr contract

- **stdout:** raw interleaved float32 PCM only (Electron does not parse helper stdout). Mid-recording delivery gaps are zero-filled into the same FIFO as real PCM (capped; before the resuming buffer) so silence does not collapse the timeline and writer starvation cannot reorder fill.
- **stderr:** JSON status, diagnostics, warnings, errors — parsed by `backend/audio/swift_audio_capture.py`.

CoreAudio may expose multi-channel buffers; preserve helper interleaved normalization and Python mixer **one-sided stereo repair** so desktop speech survives MLX/ffmpeg mono downmix.

## Permissions (do not conflate)

- CoreAudio tap → System Audio Recording for `com.avanevis.app.audiocapture-helper`.
- ScreenCaptureKit fallback → Screen Recording.
- Preflight skips proactive Screen Recording and must report `skipped` / `granted: null`, not a false grant.
- Inspect `helperCaptureBackend` and helper diagnostics before blaming “missing desktop audio” on generic screen-recording issues.

## Packaging checklist

- Build: `swift build -c release --arch arm64` in `swift/AudioCaptureHelper`.
- Stage via `build/prepare-resources.js` → `build/resources/bin`.
- Bundle/sign as `Contents/Resources/bin/audiocapture-helper` in electron-builder.

`docs/initiatives/MACOS_AUDIO_ARCHITECTURE.md` describes **future** ideas (streaming to disk, app-specific capture); do not treat planned sections as shipped behavior.
